The paper describes a web-based system that collects and provides data about Brazilian scientific production in Computer Science, specifically focusing on research papers published in selected conferences. This suggests that the paper may fall under several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). These sub-categories are all relevant to the topic of collecting and analyzing data related to computer science research, and are therefore likely candidates for this paper.
